                            <comment id="19232" author="topping" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2006 12:59:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2499&quot; title=&quot;HibernateTemplate.createSessionProxy() should return proxy implementing SessionImplementor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2499&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2499&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19240" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 01:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! We expose SessionImplementor there as well now, provided that the underlying Session implements the interface as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19241" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 01:03:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that you can also switch HibernateTemplate&apos;s &quot;exposeNativeSession&quot; flag to &quot;true&quot;, to get the native Session passed into HibernateCallbacks as-is.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19252" author="topping" created="Tue, 29 Aug 2006 06:37:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes I saw the exposeNativeSession flag, but didn&apos;t want to lose the advantages of the proxy, so I thought I would go through the process of building (painful with Maven!) and testing the patch.  Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Brian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
